sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Route as Route ({username}-notebook)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Git as GitHub/GitLab<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as Database<br/>5432/TCP PostgreSQL

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Notebook Access
    User->>Router: HTTPS Request (no auth)
    Router->>Route: Forward to Route
    Route->>OAuth: HTTPS/8443<br/>OpenShift OAuth redirect
    OAuth-->>User: OAuth login prompt
    User->>OAuth: OAuth credentials
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate token
    OAuth->>Jupyter: HTTP/8888<br/>plaintext (localhost trusted)
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI
    OAuth-->>User: WebSocket tunnel<br/>OAuth token validated

    Note over Jupyter,S3: Flow 2: Notebook to S3 Storage
    Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/data.csv<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>AWS Signature V4 (Access Key)
    S3-->>Jupyter: Data file<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over Jupyter,Git: Flow 3: Git Repository Clone
    Jupyter->>Git: git clone<br/>HTTPS/443 or SSH/22<br/>Personal Access Token or SSH Key
    Git-->>Jupyter: Repository contents<br/>HTTPS/443 or SSH/22

    Note over Jupyter,KFP: Flow 4: Pipeline Execution (Elyra Runtime)
    Jupyter->>KFP: POST /api/v1/pipelines<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    KFP->>KFP: Create Argo/Tekton Workflow
    KFP->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>AWS IAM or Access Key
    S3-->>KFP: Artifact stored
    KFP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline run ID

    Note over Jupyter,DB: Flow 5: Database Connection
    Jupyter->>DB: SELECT query<br/>PostgreSQL/5432<br/>TLS 1.2+ (if configured)<br/>Username + Password
    DB-->>Jupyter: Query results<br/>PostgreSQL/5432
